{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place coconut milk, chia seeds, syrup and one-third of the banana into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>8 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr> or until smooth and combined. Transfer into a bowl and set aside for 1 hour to allow chia seeds to expand.","Slice remaining banana into 12 slices. Place a spoonful of the reserved coconut chia mixture into the bottom of 6 ice block moulds (100 ml). Place 1 banana slice on top of the mixture. Repeat layering of remaining banana slices and coconut chia mixture. Gently tap moulds on benchtop to remove any air pockets.","Insert a popsicle stick into each mould. Place into freezer for a minimum of 6 hours or overnight, until frozen. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place chocolate into mixing bowl and grate <nobr>8 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then melt <nobr>3 min\/60°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Remove ice blocks from moulds and dip the top of each ice block into melted dark chocolate. Allow to set, then serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["400 g coconut milk","40 g chia seeds","60 g pure maple syrup","1 banana","160 g dark chocolate, broken into pieces"]}],"id":"r122255","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-LE9yxXYgTJk\/XZWfCbx5xqI\/AAAAAAAAe9w\/CIRy3xAOZDI0VmVI9cI57mmlWu00JPJPgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_mdOfhfNIWI2Ov8um.png","title":"Banana coconut ice blocks","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.8 g","fat":"14.4 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"29 g","calories":"1075 kJ \/ 256 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, 6 ice block moulds (100 ml), popsicle sticks , freezer","hintsAndTricks":["If you are going to refreeze the ice blocks after dipping in chocolate, remove them from the freezer 10-20 minutes beforehand to soften to your preferred consistency before serving. Only thaw as many ice blocks as you intend to eat, as refreezing leftovers after they have softened can be a safety hazard."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","7h 15m","6 portions"]}